text: The River Garry () is a major tributary of the River Tummel, itself a tributary of the River Tay, in the traditional county of Perthshire in the Scottish Highlands.Ordnance Survey 1:50,000 scale Landranger map sheets 42 Loch Rannoch & 43 Braemar == References == Category:Rivers of Scotland
title: River Garry, Perthshire
